Mass cremations have been taking place next to the Bagmati river which divides Kathmandu . 
  Hundreds of bodies were burned in the ghats beside the river today as the death toll stands at more than 4,000 . 
  The wood necessary to build the pyres has started to run out . 
  Families are desperate to give their loved ones the honourable send-off . 
  The sacred Hindu Pashupatinath temple is also becoming overwhelmed with bodies . 
 